    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<h3>Install Rails 3</h3>

<p>Prerequisite: Ruby</p>

<p><div class='bogus-wrapper'><notextile><figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>&lt;br/>
</span><span class='line'>$ ruby -v
</span><span class='line'>ruby 1.9.3p429 (2013-05-15 revision 40747) [x86_64-darwin12.4.0]</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure></notextile></div></p>

<p><div class='bogus-wrapper'><notextile><figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>&lt;br/>
</span><span class='line'>$ gem install rdoc ## to avoid "file 'lib' not found" error&lt;br/>
</span><span class='line'>$ gem install rails --version "=3.2.14"</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure></notextile></div></p>

<p><strong> As Aug 6th, 2013, the following installed rails 4.0.0, I chose to use Rails 3 for now. </strong>
Here is how downgrade.</p>

<p><div class='bogus-wrapper'><notextile><figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
<span class='line-number'>4</span>
<span class='line-number'>5</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>&lt;br/>
</span><span class='line'>$ gem install rails
</span><span class='line'>$ gem uninstall rails
</span><span class='line'>Successfully uninstalled rails-4.0.0
</span><span class='line'>$ gem install rails --version "=3.2.14"</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure></notextile></div></p>
